help me translate this information to make it more understandable:

@Jason Biggs Because we have to do rewrites with the overview/3* urls, the CDN isn't working out of the box. It may be helpful to add some logic to these templates so that we can set a boolean for using the CDN url or not. If we set that to true, then set the url prefix to the rocket CDN on all the images, etc.

Looks like there is a function available to pull that url from the plugin.

```
// Use this code in your template file (e.g., header.php or single.php)
if ( function_exists( 'get_rocket_option' ) ) {
    $rocketcdn_cname = get_rocket_option( 'cdn_cname' );
    if ( $rocketcdn_cname ) {
        echo esc_url( 'https://' . $rocketcdn_cname );
    }
}
```

